  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BI Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>:</p><p>- <em><strong>Develop, maintain, and optimize Tableau dashboards and reports</strong></em> based on business requirements.  </p><p>- <em><strong>Assist in data preparation, blending, and transformation for visualization.  </strong></em></p><p>- <em><strong>Work with stakeholders to gather requirements and translate them into effective visualizations.  </strong></em></p><p>- <em><strong>Troubleshoot and resolve issues</strong></em> related to <u><em>dashboards, data sources, and performance. </em></u> </p><p>- <em><strong>Ensure dashboards follow best practices for usability, performance, and design.  </strong></em></p><p>- <em><strong>Collaborate with data engineers and analysts</strong></em> to integrate data from various sources (SQL, Excel, APIs, etc.).  </p><p>- <em><strong>Document dashboard designs, data flows, and development processes.  </strong></em></p><p>- <em><strong>Stay updated with the latest Tableau features and BI trends. </strong></em> </p><p><br /><strong>Qualifications & Skills</strong>:</p><p><strong>Education</strong>: Polytechnic Diploma or bachelor’s degree in computer science, Data Analytics, Business, or a related field (or equivalent experience).  </p><p><strong>Experience</strong>: </p><p>- 0–2 years of <em><strong>experience with Tableau Desktop</strong></em> (certification is a plus).  </p><p>- <em><strong>Basic understanding of data visualization principles and dashboard design.</strong></em>  </p><p>- <em><strong>Familiarity with SQL for data querying and manipulation.  </strong></em></p><p>- Exposure to data modelling, ETL processes, or BI tools is a bonus.  </p><p><br /><strong>Technical</strong> <strong>Skills</strong>: </p><p>- <em><strong>Proficiency in Tableau</strong></em> (calculations, parameters, LOD expressions).  </p><p>- Basic knowledge of data warehousing concepts.  </p><p>- <em><strong>Experience with Excel or other data analysis tools.  </strong></em></p><p><br /><strong>Soft Skills</strong>:  </p><p>- Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.  </p><p>- Good communication skills to collaborate with non-technical teams.  </p><p>- Eagerness to learn and adapt in a fast-paced environment.  </p><p><br /><br /><strong>Nice to Have</strong>: </p><p>- Experience with Tableau Server/Online (publishing, scheduling, permissions).  </p><p>- Knowledge of Python/R for data analysis.  </p><p>- Knowledge of GitHub, GitLab</p><p>- Knowledge of Elixir Reports (Designing reports, scheduling Reports and deployment)</p><p>- Familiarity with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud).  </p><p>- Familiarity with Big Data Technology (Spark, Hadoop) </p><p>- Familiarity with Java and JavaScript</p><p>- Understanding of Agile/Scrum methodologies.<br /></p><p><br />Working Location : West<br /></p><p><em><strong>**We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes**</strong></em></p><p></p>",
